title: Chief Artificial Intelligence Officer
description: The United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) is seeking a Chief Artificial Intelligence Officer (CAIO) to advance the shared understanding of how to best implement the opportunities presented by Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML). The CAIO is the principal advisor to the Chief Information Officer (CIO) and the Deputy CIO on operationalizing AI and ML with a focus on business value delivery to the agency.

title: Chief Information Officer
description: The United States Patent & Trademark Office (USPTO) is headquartered in Alexandria, VA. title: Program Analyst (Informatics)
description: This position is located at VISN 20 Northwest Network in Vancouver, Washington, in Veteran's Health Administration (VHA) of the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA).
